==English==

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: hônt
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /hɔːnt/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /hO:nt/
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɔːnt|-ɔːnt]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# To [[inhabit]], or visit frequently (most often used in reference to ghosts).
# To make [[uneasy]].
#:''The memory of his past failures haunted him.''
# To [[stalk]], to [[follow]]
#:''The policeman haunted him, following him everywhere.''

